4
00:00:54.388 --> 00:00:56.807
We don't know why we are here.

5
00:01:05.649 --> 00:01:08.569
We don't know who
built the Silo.

6
00:01:18.871 --> 00:01:24.376
We don't know why everything
outside the Silo is the way it is.

7
00:01:25.711 --> 00:01:26.920
Good morning. Sheriff.

8
00:01:27.796 --> 00:01:30.132
Morning. Sam. Are you up yet?

9
00:01:31.425 --> 00:01:32.801
Getting there.

10
00:01:38.932 --> 00:01:42.769
We don't know when it
will be safe to go out.

11
00:01:45.772 --> 00:01:47.149
We only know that that day...

12
00:01:49.484 --> 00:01:51.737
has not come yet.

13
00:02:03.081 --> 00:02:07.961
"Double the amount of flowers
in front of the mirror."

14
00:02:28.065 --> 00:02:29.066
Hi.

15
00:02:29.149 --> 00:02:30.150
You're early.

16
00:02:30.234 --> 00:02:33.320
Yeah. I couldn't sleep.
Those damn leg cramps.

17
00:02:33.403 --> 00:02:35.531
When you get your coffee.
meet me in Cell 3.

18
00:02:35.614 --> 00:02:36.657
3?

19
00:02:38.325 --> 00:02:40.410
"Cell 3"

20
00:03:13.652 --> 00:03:15.028
Do you want some coffee?

21
00:03:17.948 --> 00:03:19.283
What are you doing?

22
00:03:19.366 --> 00:03:20.534
I want to see it.

23
00:03:21.201 --> 00:03:22.661
No. Sheriff.

24
00:03:23.245 --> 00:03:27.374
I should have done this 3
years ago. but I didn't listen.

25
00:03:27.457 --> 00:03:29.126
Wait. Stop.

26
00:03:30.544 --> 00:03:34.965
Get out of there.
Let's discuss this.

27
00:03:36.800 --> 00:03:38.594
My mind is made up. otherwise
I wouldn't have come here.

28
00:03:39.636 --> 00:03:40.846
I'm sorry. Sam.

29
00:03:42.181 --> 00:03:45.225
Are you going to say that to me
after everything we've been through?

30
00:03:45.309 --> 00:03:46.852
Do you want me to wait
until Sandy gets here?

31
00:03:46.935 --> 00:03:49.563
I don't want you to say it.

32
00:03:51.607 --> 00:03:54.860
Please. Sheriff. Don't say it.

33
00:03:54.943 --> 00:03:56.320
- Deputy Marnes...
- Please. Sheriff.

34
00:03:56.403 --> 00:03:57.529
I want to go out.

35
00:04:08.916 --> 00:04:11.335
While you get that ready.
I think I'll lie down.

36
00:05:49.433 --> 00:05:51.560
"Based on the book
series by Hugh Howey"

37
00:06:17.878 --> 00:06:19.129
Are you going to
bring the coffee?

38
00:06:19.213 --> 00:06:20.214
"Mine - Mine too"

39
00:06:20.297 --> 00:06:21.298
Yes. of course!

40
00:06:21.381 --> 00:06:24.009
Okay. I'll take it with milk. please.
Actually. I don't want it. No...

41
00:06:24.510 --> 00:06:26.303
I don't need milk. No.

42
00:06:26.386 --> 00:06:28.180
- Come on. It's almost 8.
- Okay.

43
00:06:28.722 --> 00:06:30.182
- Please.
- Okay. I'm coming.

44
00:06:32.476 --> 00:06:33.477
Thank you.

45
00:06:35.062 --> 00:06:36.146
I don't know why
we're doing this.

46
00:06:36.230 --> 00:06:38.607
We're not going to get
it. We've tried twice.

47
00:06:43.987 --> 00:06:45.405
"New message - Open. Silo Mail"

48
00:06:45.489 --> 00:06:47.282
"You have been granted permission
to conceive. congratulations"

49
00:06:47.366 --> 00:06:48.367
"You have been approved"

50
00:06:52.621 --> 00:06:54.039
I can't believe it.

51
00:06:54.623 --> 00:06:55.666
Third time's the charm.

52
00:06:55.749 --> 00:06:57.709
You're just excited
to have sex every day.

53
00:06:57.793 --> 00:06:59.545
Wait. you might be
pregnant a month from now.

54
00:06:59.628 --> 00:07:01.171
I hope it takes that long.

55
00:07:06.134 --> 00:07:07.719
You know I love you no
matter what happens.

56
00:07:08.554 --> 00:07:10.931
Shut up. We're going
to do this. Let's go.

57
00:07:11.682 --> 00:07:14.101
Allie. his office
won't open for an hour.

58
00:07:14.184 --> 00:07:15.853
Yeah. we can have
some breakfast.

59
00:07:15.936 --> 00:07:17.437
We can discuss baby names.

60
00:07:17.521 --> 00:07:20.190
And that means I'm just
going to humor you.

61
00:07:20.274 --> 00:07:22.234
because if I'm going to give
birth to this little creature.

62
00:07:22.317 --> 00:07:24.194
I'm going to name
it what I want.

63
00:07:26.071 --> 00:07:27.072
Okay.

64
00:07:29.324 --> 00:07:32.286
"Fertility window time: 364
days. 23 hours. 59 minutes"

65
00:07:37.749 --> 00:07:39.585
- Good luck.
- Thank you.

66
00:07:40.335 --> 00:07:42.171
- Congratulations.
- Yeah. thanks.

67
00:07:42.254 --> 00:07:43.255
Thank you.

68
00:07:46.008 --> 00:07:46.925
Hi.

69
00:07:47.426 --> 00:07:48.343
Hi. Congratulations.

70
00:07:49.970 --> 00:07:51.013
Hi.

71
00:07:54.725 --> 00:07:56.602
I really hate this part.

72
00:07:56.685 --> 00:07:58.270
People are just happy for us.

73
00:07:58.353 --> 00:08:00.856
I wish nobody knew.

74
00:08:03.025 --> 00:08:04.026
Damn.

75
00:08:04.109 --> 00:08:06.236
Sheriff and Mrs. Becker.

76
00:08:06.320 --> 00:08:08.280
I don't mean to interfere.

77
00:08:08.363 --> 00:08:09.489
Then don't interfere.

78
00:08:10.282 --> 00:08:12.743
There is your
famous blunt style.

79
00:08:12.826 --> 00:08:13.911
That's why everyone loves you.

80
00:08:13.994 --> 00:08:15.954
If everyone loves me. that
means I'm not doing my job.

81
00:08:17.915 --> 00:08:21.335
Mrs. Becker. your husband might not
be interested in what I want to say...

82
00:08:21.418 --> 00:08:22.753
What I really care about

83
00:08:22.836 --> 00:08:24.922
- is that you leave us alone. Gloria.
- Holston.

84
00:08:25.005 --> 00:08:27.257
But whatever the
Sheriff tells you.

85
00:08:27.341 --> 00:08:29.051
I provide fertility
counseling...

86
00:08:29.134 --> 00:08:30.761
Really? Like what?

87
00:08:31.345 --> 00:08:33.138
Your husband is waiting
for me to say something

88
00:08:33.222 --> 00:08:35.265
that I am not legally
allowed to say.

89
00:08:35.349 --> 00:08:37.643
- Like what?
- Smart.

90
00:08:37.726 --> 00:08:40.729
I don't want to be sent
outside. Thank you. Sheriff.

91
00:08:41.855 --> 00:08:45.859
Mrs. Becker. if your mind
is open. come and see me.

92
00:08:47.611 --> 00:08:49.071
Good luck to you both.

93
00:08:52.282 --> 00:08:53.659
What exactly are you doing?

94
00:08:53.742 --> 00:08:56.036
You're overpromising people
that they'll have a baby

95
00:08:56.119 --> 00:08:59.122
if they do as you say. and
that's fraud and cruelty.

96
00:09:07.673 --> 00:09:09.049
I'll let her get numb.

97
00:09:10.801 --> 00:09:16.515
Now. after removing the contraceptive
device. you'll need 2 or 3 weeks

98
00:09:16.598 --> 00:09:17.975
for your hormones to reset.

99
00:09:18.517 --> 00:09:20.727
However. some couples
succeed in getting pregnant

100
00:09:20.811 --> 00:09:22.229
within days of
getting permission.

101
00:09:22.312 --> 00:09:24.022
But you both know all that.

102
00:09:24.106 --> 00:09:25.858
Is this your second attempt?

103
00:09:26.733 --> 00:09:28.151
- Third.
- And the last one.

104
00:09:28.652 --> 00:09:30.320
I'm almost 38.

105
00:09:33.198 --> 00:09:34.283
Do you feel this?

106
00:09:35.075 --> 00:09:36.285
Just pressure.

107
00:09:36.368 --> 00:09:40.455
Okay. even though you're
numb. it will feel strange.

108
00:09:41.039 --> 00:09:43.917
We make sure to implant
the capsule deep

109
00:09:45.294 --> 00:09:47.212
so it doesn't cause
you any trouble.

110
00:09:48.630 --> 00:09:52.509
But not for long.
because I'm done.

111
00:09:54.178 --> 00:09:55.220
Here it is.

112
00:09:55.888 --> 00:09:57.639
You are no longer forbidden
from getting pregnant.

113
00:10:00.893 --> 00:10:02.728
You are now free
to have a child.

114
00:10:14.531 --> 00:10:16.533
Thank you. Mrs. Floris.

115
00:10:16.617 --> 00:10:19.995
I swear. if I hear someone
else congratulate us...

116
00:10:20.621 --> 00:10:22.122
Get me pregnant. Now.

117
00:10:22.206 --> 00:10:23.123
Yes. my lady.

118
00:10:25.000 --> 00:10:27.085
- Wait. hold on.
- What?

119
00:10:27.794 --> 00:10:28.795
Do you remember the last time?

120
00:10:28.879 --> 00:10:31.381
At some point. you'll start
feeling like this is a chore.

121
00:10:31.465 --> 00:10:32.591
Best chore ever.

122
00:10:33.342 --> 00:10:36.845
"Fertility window time: 364
days. 17 hours. 35 minutes"

123
00:10:36.929 --> 00:10:40.516
"Fertility window time: 342
days. 22 hours. 14 minutes"

124
00:10:41.558 --> 00:10:44.478
We tried 4 times before
finally getting permission.

125
00:10:44.561 --> 00:10:45.771
so this is your chance.

126
00:10:45.854 --> 00:10:46.855
Yeah. I hope so.

127
00:10:46.939 --> 00:10:47.940
"Property of Sheriff (Becker)"

128
00:10:48.023 --> 00:10:49.024
My cousin Charlene

129
00:10:49.107 --> 00:10:52.110
convinced her husband that he
had to paint his penis blue.

130
00:10:52.194 --> 00:10:53.195
Did it work?

131
00:10:53.278 --> 00:10:54.363
They succeeded in
getting pregnant.

132
00:10:54.446 --> 00:10:55.489
"Mother"

133
00:10:55.572 --> 00:10:57.533
But I'm sure that his blue
penis had nothing to do with it.

134
00:10:57.616 --> 00:11:00.494
She was just messing with him. This
shows you a picture of their wedding.

135
00:11:00.577 --> 00:11:02.788
- Hi. Bernard.
- Good morning. Bernard.

136
00:11:02.871 --> 00:11:04.498
Karen and Allison.

137
00:11:05.624 --> 00:11:07.584
I see you posted an article

138
00:11:07.668 --> 00:11:10.796
on the bulletin board about
recovering deleted files.

139
00:11:10.879 --> 00:11:13.423
- That's right.
- You know you need my approval

140
00:11:13.507 --> 00:11:16.343
for any technical content
before posting it.

141
00:11:16.426 --> 00:11:19.388
Well. I thought we could
reduce service calls

142
00:11:19.471 --> 00:11:21.640
if people could solve
some problems themselves.

143
00:11:23.559 --> 00:11:25.394
I removed your post.

144
00:11:25.477 --> 00:11:28.438
I don't doubt your
good intentions.

145
00:11:28.522 --> 00:11:31.900
but our reporting system
exists for a logical reason.

146
00:11:31.984 --> 00:11:33.151
I understand.

147
00:11:35.195 --> 00:11:36.572
A damn bastard.

148
00:11:37.114 --> 00:11:38.782
Did you know you were
breaking the rules?

149
00:11:38.866 --> 00:11:43.161
No. Maybe. Sort of.

150
00:11:44.788 --> 00:11:46.331
There are a lot of rules.

151
00:11:46.415 --> 00:11:47.791
You wanted to work
in the IT department.

152
00:11:47.875 --> 00:11:50.711
Not just the IT
department. but everywhere.

153
00:11:52.880 --> 00:11:56.175
We blame the rebels for
erasing our history. right?

154
00:11:56.258 --> 00:11:57.426
Yeah.

155
00:11:57.509 --> 00:12:00.179
Then why can't we ask
questions about that history?

156
00:12:00.262 --> 00:12:02.368
And if losing our history
is so bad. why would

157
00:12:02.451 --> 00:12:04.558
the Judicial Authority
have hired thugs send you

158
00:12:04.641 --> 00:12:05.934
to work in the mines

159
00:12:06.018 --> 00:12:08.061
if you possessed an old
artifact from the Old Era?

160
00:12:08.145 --> 00:12:09.146
Allison.

161
00:12:10.772 --> 00:12:12.024
Really?

162
00:12:12.107 --> 00:12:14.151
Are you going to use the
Sheriff's tone with me?

163
00:12:14.902 --> 00:12:17.613
Honey. the Pact is
our only history.

164
00:12:19.031 --> 00:12:21.783
What if some rebels decided they
wanted to see for themselves

165
00:12:21.867 --> 00:12:22.868
what life is like above ground?

166
00:12:23.452 --> 00:12:26.538
If they somehow managed to open
that door. we would be finished.

167
00:12:27.915 --> 00:12:30.292
Part of my job is to make
sure that doesn't happen.

168
00:12:53.524 --> 00:12:55.317
"Fertility window time: 157
days. 22 hours. 14 minutes"

169
00:12:57.277 --> 00:12:58.779
"(Allison) and
(Holston). May 5. '26"

170
00:13:05.786 --> 00:13:06.787
My period started.

171
00:13:07.913 --> 00:13:10.249
I know. We still have time.

172
00:13:16.463 --> 00:13:18.173
What are you afraid of?

173
00:13:18.257 --> 00:13:21.802
I'm afraid that a drunk teenager
obsessed with fires with a firework

174
00:13:21.885 --> 00:13:24.680
could start a fire
that causes mass panic.

175
00:13:25.681 --> 00:13:27.850
Are you done? Can I speak?

176
00:13:27.933 --> 00:13:30.143
Ever since I put on the Mayor's scarf
and we put on the Sheriff's badge.

177
00:13:30.227 --> 00:13:33.689
Freedom Day has passed without problems.
And it has been a long time since then.

178
00:13:33.772 --> 00:13:35.315
All the deputies will
be on their patrols.

179
00:13:35.399 --> 00:13:37.442
and fire teams will be
ready on every tenth level.

180
00:13:40.112 --> 00:13:42.865
It gets harder to see
the outside every month.

181
00:13:42.948 --> 00:13:45.659
A long time between cleanings
means things are going well.

182
00:13:46.326 --> 00:13:47.619
No one wants to clean.

183
00:13:49.037 --> 00:13:51.331
but people need to see
the situation outside.

184
00:14:03.427 --> 00:14:04.428
Mrs. Becker.

185
00:14:04.511 --> 00:14:06.013
- Hi.
- I was looking for you.

186
00:14:06.638 --> 00:14:09.808
- Are you pregnant?
- Not yet.

187
00:14:09.892 --> 00:14:12.019
But I'm afraid I
won't need your help.

188
00:14:12.102 --> 00:14:13.270
- Take care of yourself.
- No.

189
00:14:13.353 --> 00:14:18.650
That's not why I was looking for you. I
want to ask you a question in private.

190
00:14:25.782 --> 00:14:29.328
I hate the term "Freedom
Day". Too simple.

191
00:14:30.120 --> 00:14:32.623
"Rebellion Suppression
Day" is more accurate.

192
00:14:33.123 --> 00:14:35.209
Ma'am. you said you
wanted to ask a question.

193
00:14:38.504 --> 00:14:39.630
Why did I do this?

194
00:14:39.713 --> 00:14:41.423
Because I don't
want them to hear.

195
00:14:42.007 --> 00:14:43.008
Who?

196
00:14:43.509 --> 00:14:44.968
Who has listening devices?

197
00:14:45.844 --> 00:14:46.845
The Judicial Authority?

198
00:14:51.683 --> 00:14:56.271
Have you ever wondered what
was on the records they erased?

199
00:14:56.355 --> 00:15:01.944
In the books they burned? If
the rebels even did that at all?

200
00:15:03.445 --> 00:15:05.280
- I have to go to work.
- Please.

201
00:15:05.364 --> 00:15:06.949
I didn't ask you to
come here on a whim.

202
00:15:08.367 --> 00:15:10.911
I heard that you.
too. are a person

203
00:15:12.120 --> 00:15:13.121
who has questions.

204
00:15:15.707 --> 00:15:16.708
Who told you that?

205
00:15:16.792 --> 00:15:18.669
Why do we live underground?

206
00:15:18.752 --> 00:15:22.214
What really happened outside?

207
00:15:22.798 --> 00:15:24.675
- I'm leaving now.
- There is one more thing.

208
00:15:26.426 --> 00:15:30.055
Do you really think you are the
person they want to have children?

209
00:15:33.433 --> 00:15:35.644
3 times without success?

210
00:15:36.228 --> 00:15:39.606
She just said it and I started feeling
like it's happening on purpose.

211
00:15:39.690 --> 00:15:43.402
Okay. Her condition has officially
deteriorated from eccentric

212
00:15:43.485 --> 00:15:45.028
to completely insane.

213
00:15:45.696 --> 00:15:46.822
I should send the
psychological team

214
00:15:46.905 --> 00:15:49.658
- to visit Gloria.
- Don't. She's just...

215
00:15:49.741 --> 00:15:52.286
She's what? Did she say
something that bothered you?

216
00:15:52.369 --> 00:15:54.788
She and her husband
couldn't have a baby.

217
00:15:54.872 --> 00:15:56.790
She wants you to find out why.

218
00:15:57.291 --> 00:15:59.751
They removed the contraceptive
device from you. Ali.

219
00:16:00.252 --> 00:16:04.631
We have the same chance of having a
child as anyone who got permission.

220
00:16:05.841 --> 00:16:07.509
- Agreed?
- Agreed.

221
00:16:19.438 --> 00:16:20.772
You're not going to like this.

222
00:16:20.856 --> 00:16:24.902
Our friend George sent another ticket.
Guess whose turn it is to deal with him.

223
00:16:30.866 --> 00:16:33.702
He's a programmer in the mid-levels
and has a repair kiosk in the market.

224
00:16:33.785 --> 00:16:34.729
Why do you have to go?

225
00:16:34.812 --> 00:16:36.788
Everyone takes a
holiday for Freedom Day.

226
00:16:36.872 --> 00:16:39.958
And because you're working. I
thought I'd be ready to work.

227
00:16:40.042 --> 00:16:41.960
But he wants me to be
there early in the morning.

228
00:16:42.044 --> 00:16:44.963
which means I have to go tonight
and book a room at the inn.

229
00:16:45.047 --> 00:16:49.927
And that also means that we'll
miss our nightly entertainment.

230
00:16:53.847 --> 00:16:55.599
- Honey.
- I know. I'll stay calm.

231
00:16:56.558 --> 00:16:58.393
- Not here.
- Yes. here.

232
00:16:58.477 --> 00:17:00.354
- Honey. Marnes...
- Let's be quick.

233
00:17:00.437 --> 00:17:01.438
Okay.

234
00:17:05.192 --> 00:17:06.359
It's okay.

235
00:17:26.630 --> 00:17:27.631
"Sheriff"

236
00:17:31.093 --> 00:17:32.094
Damn it.

237
00:17:33.387 --> 00:17:36.139
If I don't get pregnant
after this. I never will.

238
00:17:55.200 --> 00:17:58.829
We will beat you to the top and we
will open the door to the outside

239
00:17:58.912 --> 00:18:01.707
and let all the
poison into the Silo!

240
00:18:04.168 --> 00:18:05.419
No. rebel!

241
00:18:05.502 --> 00:18:08.422
In the name of the Founders!

242
00:19:16.323 --> 00:19:19.576
"Computer Repairs"

243
00:19:22.204 --> 00:19:23.288
"Allison Becker"?

244
00:19:23.372 --> 00:19:24.540
Yes. You must be...

245
00:19:24.623 --> 00:19:27.000
I've been looking forward to
meeting you for a long time.

246
00:19:34.424 --> 00:19:36.885
I'm sorry for forcing you
to come here on Freedom Day.

247
00:19:36.969 --> 00:19:39.847
I'm working and my
husband is working. so...

248
00:19:39.930 --> 00:19:41.849
That's what I thought.
because he's the Sheriff.

249
00:19:41.932 --> 00:19:43.308
And that's why I thought I
had a chance to bring you in.

250
00:19:44.643 --> 00:19:47.688
I don't understand.
How can I help you?

251
00:19:48.313 --> 00:19:51.733
Yeah. I read your post about
how to recover deleted files.

252
00:19:52.276 --> 00:19:56.321
I felt like it wouldn't be
available for long. so I printed it.

253
00:19:57.573 --> 00:20:00.701
- That must have cost you a lot.
- Yeah. it's worth every coin.

254
00:20:00.784 --> 00:20:01.952
I really benefited from it.

255
00:20:03.203 --> 00:20:07.207
But I wanted to see you personally.
so I sent a repair request

256
00:20:07.291 --> 00:20:08.500
and I was hoping you'd come.

257
00:20:08.584 --> 00:20:12.087
Of course. they sent everyone except
you. So I thought that on the holiday...

258
00:20:12.171 --> 00:20:13.547
Why didn't you
just ask to see me?

259
00:20:14.047 --> 00:20:15.591
I didn't want to
raise suspicions.

260
00:20:16.842 --> 00:20:17.843
From whom?

261
00:20:17.926 --> 00:20:19.553
From the people who wrote
the laws about artifacts?

262
00:20:20.304 --> 00:20:22.264
Are you worried about
the Judicial Authority?

263
00:20:22.973 --> 00:20:23.974
Isn't that everyone?

264
00:20:25.434 --> 00:20:26.602
Is it about an artifact?

265
00:20:26.685 --> 00:20:28.270
That's the problem.
I don't know.

266
00:20:30.939 --> 00:20:34.067
A man brought this thing

267
00:20:35.027 --> 00:20:36.486
about a year ago.

268
00:20:37.946 --> 00:20:40.782
He said he found it under
the rug in a closet.

269
00:20:41.909 --> 00:20:44.494
I turned it on and
it seemed empty.

270
00:20:45.078 --> 00:20:47.581
Then I tried the
method you posted...

271
00:20:48.999 --> 00:20:50.000
"Connecting Device"

272
00:20:50.083 --> 00:20:54.713
...and I was able
to check the memory.

273
00:20:55.797 --> 00:20:57.090
"Scanning"

274
00:20:58.800 --> 00:21:03.847
It said the hard drive was mostly
used. but I don't see any files.

275
00:21:05.098 --> 00:21:08.018
There is something on it. but
I don't know how to access it.

276
00:21:08.101 --> 00:21:10.354
It could be old family recipes.

277
00:21:10.437 --> 00:21:13.524
Then they are very
old family recipes.

278
00:21:14.733 --> 00:21:15.984
I checked the log in
the IT department.

279
00:21:16.818 --> 00:21:18.737
There is no registration
for this serial number.

280
00:21:19.738 --> 00:21:23.158
Of course. the log started
after the rebellion.

281
00:21:23.242 --> 00:21:25.869
Do you think this hard drive
is more than 140 years old?

282
00:21:25.953 --> 00:21:28.997
That's impossible. All hard drives
were destroyed in the rebellion.

283
00:21:29.081 --> 00:21:30.415
It could be a data error.

284
00:21:32.459 --> 00:21:34.628
Or maybe not.

285
00:21:38.549 --> 00:21:42.469
It could simply be finding
the name in the directory.

286
00:21:42.553 --> 00:21:43.554
Let me see.

287
00:21:45.097 --> 00:21:46.598
Is there anything I can...

288
00:21:46.682 --> 00:21:48.392
Not talking would be helpful.

289
00:21:59.862 --> 00:22:02.447
- Happy Freedom Day.
- Happy Freedom Day. Mayor.

290
00:22:02.531 --> 00:22:03.866
I was glad to see you all.

291
00:22:36.398 --> 00:22:38.650
Do you have any
idea what 18 means?

292
00:22:38.734 --> 00:22:39.735
No.

293
00:22:44.239 --> 00:22:48.368
- Do you have a magnifying glass?
- Yes.

294
00:23:07.638 --> 00:23:08.889
6 minutes

295
00:23:09.473 --> 00:23:11.141
and 6 seconds

296
00:23:11.850 --> 00:23:13.477
after 6 o'clock

297
00:23:14.144 --> 00:23:15.687
on this day

298
00:23:16.188 --> 00:23:19.650
140 years ago.

299
00:23:19.733 --> 00:23:24.321
This is the moment we
regained our freedom.

300
00:23:27.699 --> 00:23:30.786
We gather on this anniversary

301
00:23:31.328 --> 00:23:34.081
to remember the horror
of the rebellion.

302
00:23:35.123 --> 00:23:36.959
If they had succeeded

303
00:23:37.042 --> 00:23:40.838
in opening the door
to the outside world.

304
00:23:40.921 --> 00:23:44.258
we wouldn't be here now.

305
00:23:45.717 --> 00:23:49.763
We thank the Founders
because they didn't succeed.

306
00:23:49.847 --> 00:23:53.475
but they succeeded in
taking our history away.

307
00:23:53.559 --> 00:23:55.060
Do you have something stronger?

308
00:23:55.686 --> 00:23:57.312
This is the strongest I have.

309
00:23:59.022 --> 00:24:00.399
It's letters. but...

310
00:24:01.483 --> 00:24:02.442
"(AT 501334) - Library"

311
00:24:02.526 --> 00:24:04.152
I think it says "Library" on it.

312
00:24:06.613 --> 00:24:09.199
They destroyed our
computer hard drives.

313
00:24:09.783 --> 00:24:14.496
They cut up our files and burned
all the books in our libraries.

314
00:24:14.580 --> 00:24:16.206
"Searching the directory
for the mystery puzzle"

315
00:24:18.500 --> 00:24:21.545
"Device Name: 18 - Type:
Data - Number of files: 269"

316
00:24:26.925 --> 00:24:30.053
"Silo Blueprint -
October 12. Silo Year 98"

317
00:24:30.137 --> 00:24:31.930
But they stopped them.

318
00:24:32.556 --> 00:24:36.476
Our heroic ancestors
saved the day.

319
00:24:38.395 --> 00:24:40.898
"Levels 1 - 20.
Loading upper levels"

320
00:24:43.108 --> 00:24:44.443
Look at this.

321
00:24:50.532 --> 00:24:51.533
I won't look.

322
00:24:52.534 --> 00:24:53.535
You shouldn't either.

323
00:24:54.286 --> 00:24:55.787
You must bury it.

324
00:24:56.371 --> 00:24:58.165
Bury it? Are you kidding?
This is the greatest...

325
00:24:58.248 --> 00:25:01.460
It's an artifact. Just
possessing it is against the law.

326
00:25:01.543 --> 00:25:03.795
But it could be the key to
everything we don't know.

327
00:25:03.879 --> 00:25:04.577
We have to see...

328
00:25:04.660 --> 00:25:06.840
They might send you outside
to clean because of this.

329
00:25:06.924 --> 00:25:09.760
Are you going to
tell your husband?

330
00:25:10.677 --> 00:25:11.678
Just get rid of it.

331
00:25:30.489 --> 00:25:32.616
And their great victory

332
00:25:33.200 --> 00:25:36.745
we must celebrate with cheers.

333
00:25:53.804 --> 00:25:57.766
We must celebrate
it with trumpets.

334
00:26:13.198 --> 00:26:14.783
Where does this lead
for heaven's sake?

335
00:26:15.868 --> 00:26:18.537
"Secret tunnel"

336
00:26:28.672 --> 00:26:33.552
And we must remember
it in silence.

337
00:26:55.240 --> 00:26:59.119
"Hear this echo

338
00:26:59.203 --> 00:27:01.830
It calls to us

339
00:27:01.914 --> 00:27:05.918
to our duty

340
00:27:06.001 --> 00:27:09.421
Hear the voices singing

341
00:27:09.505 --> 00:27:12.508
loudly with pride

342
00:27:12.591 --> 00:27:16.303
Praise the beauty of freedom

343
00:27:16.386 --> 00:27:20.516
and see the bright light

344
00:27:24.353 --> 00:27:28.732
from that long night rising"

345
00:27:40.285 --> 00:27:42.955
Sorry. I'm just...

346
00:27:43.956 --> 00:27:46.083
I'm very tired from the climb.

347
00:27:47.709 --> 00:27:50.879
I think if I hadn't been sitting
all day. I'd be more agile.

348
00:27:53.674 --> 00:27:54.675
Yeah.

349
00:27:56.802 --> 00:27:58.053
I'm just saying I'm tired.

350
00:27:59.096 --> 00:28:00.097
Yeah.

351
00:28:01.640 --> 00:28:03.559
Are you tired from
climbing 70 floors

352
00:28:03.642 --> 00:28:04.643
or are you...

353
00:28:06.770 --> 00:28:07.896
tired of this?

354
00:28:10.732 --> 00:28:12.025
We still have plenty of time.

355
00:28:12.568 --> 00:28:14.444
This must not be
fun for you anymore.

356
00:28:15.279 --> 00:28:16.572
It's not about fun.

357
00:28:19.032 --> 00:28:20.450
I want to have a child.

358
00:28:23.579 --> 00:28:24.580
I wanted that too.

359
00:28:52.357 --> 00:28:53.609
How did it go with George?

360
00:28:54.818 --> 00:28:55.861
I couldn't help him.

361
00:28:56.862 --> 00:28:58.113
I think he's just lonely.

362
00:28:58.197 --> 00:29:00.407
He wants to talk to others
who understand computers.

363
00:29:06.079 --> 00:29:08.749
You know? I don't know
if it's something I ate

364
00:29:08.832 --> 00:29:12.044
or if I caught a cold.
but I don't feel well.

365
00:29:12.127 --> 00:29:14.004
Go home. I'll tell Bernard.

366
00:29:15.839 --> 00:29:16.924
Thank you.

367
00:29:19.843 --> 00:29:20.928
Get well soon.

368
00:29:52.960 --> 00:29:54.086
Come in.

369
00:30:00.342 --> 00:30:01.552
I hoped you'd come back.

370
00:30:02.344 --> 00:30:04.304
Why don't they want
us to have children?

371
00:30:18.902 --> 00:30:23.115
- Was Bernard polite?
- I didn't see him.

372
00:30:27.494 --> 00:30:30.330
I think I'll take a day off
tomorrow. I'll go to the market.

373
00:30:30.414 --> 00:30:32.666
What do you need? I
can send a porter.

374
00:30:32.749 --> 00:30:34.710
I just want to take a look.

375
00:30:35.210 --> 00:30:36.628
I'll take a little walk.

376
00:30:37.212 --> 00:30:38.589
Clear my mind from...

377
00:30:40.924 --> 00:30:43.468
Sure. Yeah.

378
00:30:43.552 --> 00:30:45.053
That sounds like a good idea.

379
00:31:08.744 --> 00:31:10.120
I want to see everything.

380
00:31:28.013 --> 00:31:29.515
My mind is exhausted.

381
00:31:35.854 --> 00:31:38.440
I don't need to tell you that
we can't tell anyone about this.

382
00:31:38.982 --> 00:31:40.025
You don't have to say that.

383
00:31:41.944 --> 00:31:43.111
When can you come back?

384
00:31:43.612 --> 00:31:44.613
I don't know.

385
00:31:50.118 --> 00:31:51.119
What is this?

386
00:31:53.413 --> 00:31:54.581
I don't know.

387
00:31:55.332 --> 00:31:56.333
The last one?

388
00:32:01.922 --> 00:32:04.842
"(Jane Carmody). Cleaning.
September 13. Silo Year 97"

389
00:32:29.032 --> 00:32:30.200
Wait! Stick to the right.

390
00:32:55.434 --> 00:32:56.435
It's late.

391
00:32:57.269 --> 00:32:58.562
I lost track of time.

392
00:32:58.645 --> 00:33:02.065
Did you go on a shopping spree?
Did you spend our whole account?

393
00:33:02.149 --> 00:33:04.526
Yeah. I wish. Next time.

394
00:33:24.922 --> 00:33:27.216
I got a message from the doctor.

395
00:33:27.299 --> 00:33:29.676
The only time he can
see us is at 11 o'clock.

396
00:33:30.761 --> 00:33:35.182
But you don't know. Technically
we still have several hours.

397
00:33:35.265 --> 00:33:36.517
It's okay.

398
00:33:36.600 --> 00:33:39.520
I'll be a little late waking
up. so I'll meet you there.

399
00:33:45.484 --> 00:33:48.362
Wait. are you okay?

400
00:33:50.405 --> 00:33:51.406
No.

401
00:33:52.491 --> 00:33:53.700
But I will be okay.

402
00:34:06.171 --> 00:34:09.174
"Fertility window time:
7 hours and 44 minutes"

403
00:34:33.197 --> 00:34:34.574
- Hi. Karen.
- Hi.

404
00:34:35.576 --> 00:34:36.577
Where is Allison?

405
00:34:38.036 --> 00:34:41.039
She sent a message with someone
that she's not feeling well.

406
00:34:43.292 --> 00:34:44.793
- Thank you.
- Okay.

407
00:34:58.140 --> 00:34:59.308
We need to talk.

408
00:35:01.685 --> 00:35:03.187
- What's wrong?
- Sit down.

409
00:35:06.440 --> 00:35:08.650
- Are you okay?
- Sit down. please.

410
00:35:17.576 --> 00:35:18.911
I was going to talk
to you last night.

411
00:35:18.994 --> 00:35:22.497
but I wasn't sure if you could
handle hearing what I wanted to say.

412
00:35:23.624 --> 00:35:25.334
You don't always listen. honey.

413
00:35:26.877 --> 00:35:27.920
What are you talking about?

414
00:35:28.003 --> 00:35:29.922
- I always listen...
- Talking means you're not listening.

415
00:35:32.257 --> 00:35:37.554
Since you're the man of the law. I thought
I should provide some proof for you.

416
00:35:38.847 --> 00:35:40.641
Proof of what?

417
00:35:41.642 --> 00:35:43.727
I can't tell you how
I know that. but...

418
00:35:45.103 --> 00:35:47.272
They will never let
us have children.

419
00:35:47.356 --> 00:35:49.316
- What?
- We are...

420
00:35:51.318 --> 00:35:54.863
I'm not the person they
want to have children.

421
00:35:55.572 --> 00:35:56.615
Who do you mean?

422
00:35:56.698 --> 00:35:59.034
The ones who wrote the Pact.

423
00:35:59.117 --> 00:36:03.038
They want obedient
and compliant people.

424
00:36:05.332 --> 00:36:07.793
I saw Dr. Leonard removing
the contraceptive device.

425
00:36:07.876 --> 00:36:10.379
- No. you didn't.
- I was there.

426
00:36:10.462 --> 00:36:11.839
It was behind a curtain.

427
00:36:11.922 --> 00:36:14.007
- You didn't see what he was doing.
- Allison...

428
00:36:14.091 --> 00:36:16.218
I assure you

429
00:36:17.803 --> 00:36:19.721
that he didn't remove
the contraceptive device.

430
00:36:20.264 --> 00:36:21.473
How do you know that?

431
00:36:21.974 --> 00:36:23.475
Because I just removed it.

432
00:36:32.025 --> 00:36:33.277
What did you do?

433
00:36:36.029 --> 00:36:38.407
Keep pressure on
it and don't move.

434
00:36:47.666 --> 00:36:48.792
Wait.

435
00:36:53.714 --> 00:36:54.715
Wait.

436
00:37:07.394 --> 00:37:08.770
- You have to come.
- What?

437
00:37:08.854 --> 00:37:10.355
It's Allison.

438
00:37:11.231 --> 00:37:13.317
- Good. Sheriff!
- I can't. Allison is injured.

439
00:37:13.400 --> 00:37:14.860
Allison is in the cafeteria.

440
00:37:18.322 --> 00:37:22.409
None of this is real.
Do you see that?

441
00:37:23.160 --> 00:37:26.038
They want to keep you
here. so they lie to you.

442
00:37:26.121 --> 00:37:29.958
The place is green outside. There
are green trees. There is a blue sky.

443
00:37:30.792 --> 00:37:33.295
There are things
flying in the air.

444
00:37:34.338 --> 00:37:35.714
Does no one hear me?

445
00:37:36.840 --> 00:37:38.008
They are keeping
us trapped here.

446
00:37:38.091 --> 00:37:40.385
- This view is a lie.
- Allison.

447
00:37:40.469 --> 00:37:43.555
- Allison. come with me.
- They want us to... no.

448
00:37:43.639 --> 00:37:45.015
- Listen to me.
- We tried...

449
00:37:45.098 --> 00:37:48.310
- We tried 3 times. I know this is hard.
- I'm not crazy!

450
00:37:48.393 --> 00:37:50.687
- Why are you treating me like I'm crazy?
- Of course I'm not.

451
00:37:50.771 --> 00:37:53.607
Allison. I've seen several patients
going through a nervous breakdown.

452
00:37:53.690 --> 00:37:55.984
I am not going through
a nervous breakdown.

453
00:37:56.068 --> 00:37:57.236
You're bleeding. honey.

454
00:37:57.319 --> 00:37:58.904
- And you have to come...
- No!

455
00:37:59.613 --> 00:38:04.701
No. I've been thinking
about this a lot. okay?

456
00:38:05.410 --> 00:38:09.915
Please. You must know that
there is no other way.

457
00:38:11.875 --> 00:38:13.085
I'm sorry. my dear.

458
00:38:14.378 --> 00:38:15.879
It's okay.

459
00:38:16.588 --> 00:38:18.465
- It's okay.
- I want to go out!

460
00:38:28.684 --> 00:38:29.935
I want to go out.

461
00:38:32.437 --> 00:38:33.438
My God.

462
00:39:06.430 --> 00:39:08.765
- There must be a solution.
- There isn't.

463
00:39:08.849 --> 00:39:12.978
We can say she was sad or
misspoke or they misheard her.

464
00:39:13.604 --> 00:39:16.982
There were people present. They
heard everything that was said.

465
00:39:17.065 --> 00:39:19.484
- Maybe we can...
- We can bribe them or kill them.

466
00:39:19.568 --> 00:39:20.652
No. for heaven's sake.

467
00:39:21.904 --> 00:39:26.033
The Pact says you can request a session
if you feel people misheard you.

468
00:39:26.116 --> 00:39:28.035
Allison doesn't feel that way.

469
00:39:28.869 --> 00:39:30.871
Don't you even want to
consider this possibility?

470
00:39:30.954 --> 00:39:32.414
Of course I do!

471
00:39:33.498 --> 00:39:37.252
Don't you two think I've thought about this
over and over? There's nothing I can do.

472
00:39:42.424 --> 00:39:46.136
If we summarize the
Pact into one law.

473
00:39:46.762 --> 00:39:51.475
it's don't say you want to go
out or you will actually go out.

474
00:39:57.272 --> 00:40:01.985
Did someone else play a role in this?
By pointing her to this opinion?

475
00:40:02.069 --> 00:40:07.407
I spoke to a fertility counselor
on level 17. Gloria Hildenbrandt.

476
00:40:07.491 --> 00:40:08.992
And what did she say?

477
00:40:09.076 --> 00:40:10.953
She admitted that she planted
the idea in Allison's mind

478
00:40:11.036 --> 00:40:14.081
about us not being the kind of people
that they want to have children.

479
00:40:14.164 --> 00:40:15.249
Who do you mean?

480
00:40:15.332 --> 00:40:16.416
She doesn't know.

481
00:40:16.500 --> 00:40:19.461
She's just angry because she and
her husband couldn't have children.

482
00:40:19.545 --> 00:40:21.088
You will speak at
the police station.

483
00:40:21.171 --> 00:40:25.300
We also brought in the man from
the market named George Wilkins.

484
00:40:25.384 --> 00:40:27.511
He runs a computer repair stall.

485
00:40:27.594 --> 00:40:30.305
Allison provided him with
support service on the holiday.

486
00:40:30.389 --> 00:40:35.769
She went shopping yesterday.
I thought she went to see him.

487
00:40:35.853 --> 00:40:38.522
But Wilkins said Allison
didn't come back.

488
00:40:39.231 --> 00:40:43.861
A team from the Judicial branch searched
his stall. but they didn't find anything.

489
00:40:45.153 --> 00:40:46.446
Why then?

490
00:40:48.490 --> 00:40:51.118
Allison has strong feelings.

491
00:40:52.995 --> 00:40:55.163
But not being able
to have a child...

492
00:40:57.499 --> 00:41:01.461
I think it was more
than she could handle.

493
00:41:07.467 --> 00:41:11.388
Holston. you don't have to
be present for the rest.

494
00:41:12.806 --> 00:41:13.807
I am the Sheriff.

495
00:41:13.891 --> 00:41:15.434
Don't you want to leave
this to someone else?

496
00:41:16.393 --> 00:41:19.354
- I took an oath when I took the job.
- I know. but everyone...

497
00:41:19.438 --> 00:41:22.858
What is the point of an oath if
you only keep it if it's easy?

498
00:41:28.864 --> 00:41:30.741
Two days off. except
for essential staff.

499
00:41:32.034 --> 00:41:34.328
Open the summit
rooms for visitors.

500
00:41:34.411 --> 00:41:38.874
We expect this to attract a larger crowd
than usual. because it's been a long time.

501
00:41:38.957 --> 00:41:42.336
We will hold a lottery to
choose the cafeteria attendees.

502
00:42:00.395 --> 00:42:01.647
I'm really sorry.

503
00:42:04.233 --> 00:42:05.234
Me too.

504
00:42:09.446 --> 00:42:10.948
I haven't lost my mind.

505
00:42:11.031 --> 00:42:13.242
You removed something from
your body with a knife.

506
00:42:13.784 --> 00:42:15.953
Yeah. and it hurt a lot.

507
00:42:20.082 --> 00:42:22.334
I took the capsule
to Dr. Leonard.

508
00:42:22.417 --> 00:42:23.794
Really? And what did he say?

509
00:42:23.877 --> 00:42:27.881
It was there to save the
spot or prevent infection.

510
00:42:27.965 --> 00:42:29.132
Something like that. right?

511
00:42:34.429 --> 00:42:35.639
It doesn't matter.

512
00:42:39.935 --> 00:42:41.603
I have to tell you something.

513
00:42:43.272 --> 00:42:44.773
But I want you to
sit next to me.

514
00:42:45.440 --> 00:42:47.693
- I don't want anyone to hear.
- We are alone.

515
00:42:48.277 --> 00:42:49.278
Please.

516
00:42:51.321 --> 00:42:52.322
Please.

517
00:43:04.126 --> 00:43:06.920
First. I love you.

518
00:43:07.004 --> 00:43:12.467
- This is the most important thing.
- Really?

519
00:43:13.051 --> 00:43:16.180
I know you're angry.
I would be angry too.

520
00:43:19.183 --> 00:43:24.188
If I could go back to the past to forget
everything I've known. I would do it.

521
00:43:25.063 --> 00:43:26.398
Without hesitation.

522
00:43:29.484 --> 00:43:33.739
But I found out that everything
they told us isn't true.

523
00:43:34.907 --> 00:43:38.493
The reason we are here and
what happened 140 years ago.

524
00:43:38.577 --> 00:43:40.058
who is entitled to have children and why.

525
00:43:40.141 --> 00:43:41.622
And that's not even
the biggest discovery...

526
00:43:41.705 --> 00:43:42.706
So?

527
00:43:43.624 --> 00:43:45.334
- So?
- If you discovered something like this.

528
00:43:45.417 --> 00:43:49.296
you should tell me or Mayor
Jahns or the Judicial.

529
00:43:49.379 --> 00:43:50.881
You should tell
everyone in the silo.

530
00:43:50.964 --> 00:43:55.302
Not say the words that will
send you outside to die.

531
00:43:55.385 --> 00:44:00.140
But this great discovery I
discovered. I won't die outside.

532
00:44:00.224 --> 00:44:06.104
Listen. they have the ability to
change what we see on the screens.

533
00:44:06.188 --> 00:44:08.524
In the cafeteria. across
the silo. and everywhere.

534
00:44:08.607 --> 00:44:10.651
- What are you talking about?
- They take the image

535
00:44:10.734 --> 00:44:12.569
and change it somehow.

536
00:44:12.653 --> 00:44:16.865
So. what we see isn't
what's really outside.

537
00:44:16.949 --> 00:44:19.785
This is what they want
us to think is outside.

538
00:44:19.868 --> 00:44:22.037
- What's that? There?
- Holston.

539
00:44:22.120 --> 00:44:23.330
And that.

540
00:44:23.413 --> 00:44:25.582
These are the last 3
people who went to clean.

541
00:44:25.666 --> 00:44:28.377
Or maybe this isn't the truth.

542
00:44:28.961 --> 00:44:32.339
- What if it's just rocks and bushes?
- I know what I see.

543
00:44:32.422 --> 00:44:35.384
Not if that's what the
computer wants you to see.

544
00:44:35.467 --> 00:44:37.886
- Why would they do that?
- To keep us here.

545
00:44:39.221 --> 00:44:40.305
Okay.

546
00:44:41.890 --> 00:44:45.686
If the place is wonderful outside.
why don't they want us to go out?

547
00:44:46.436 --> 00:44:47.563
I don't know.

548
00:44:49.690 --> 00:44:52.401
- I don't know.
- Okay.

549
00:44:52.484 --> 00:44:54.736
But I'll find out. I'm sorry.

550
00:44:55.320 --> 00:44:56.905
- You keep saying that. I...
- Okay.

551
00:44:56.989 --> 00:44:59.032
There's something else I
want you to think about

552
00:44:59.116 --> 00:45:00.325
then you should get some sleep.

553
00:45:02.578 --> 00:45:03.954
I'm not going anywhere.

554
00:45:06.123 --> 00:45:07.457
Why do they send
people to clean?

555
00:45:12.296 --> 00:45:14.923
To remove dust and
dirt from the sensors

556
00:45:15.007 --> 00:45:16.300
- so we can see.
- No.

557
00:45:16.383 --> 00:45:18.385
Why do people do it?

558
00:45:18.468 --> 00:45:20.179
Most people swear
they won't do it.

559
00:45:20.262 --> 00:45:23.140
When I arrested Brent. he said
you should shoot him in the head

560
00:45:23.223 --> 00:45:25.601
and throw him down the stairs.
because he won't go to clean.

561
00:45:25.684 --> 00:45:28.854
- And what did he do after that?
- He went out to clean.

562
00:45:28.937 --> 00:45:32.566
I think people clean
because they hope somehow

563
00:45:33.317 --> 00:45:38.572
that they will see the truth
and that this is just a lie.

564
00:45:41.533 --> 00:45:47.164
When I go out. if I find it
as I see it. I won't clean.

565
00:45:48.665 --> 00:45:51.627
I'll wave goodbye to you. because I will
have made the biggest mistake of my life.

566
00:45:52.628 --> 00:45:54.713
But if I am right

567
00:45:55.255 --> 00:45:58.008
and I find the place green.
fertile. and beautiful.

568
00:45:58.091 --> 00:46:03.597
I'll take out my rag and I'll
start cleaning and you'll know it.

569
00:46:06.141 --> 00:46:10.562
Then I'll cross the hill and
I'll find out what's happening.

570
00:46:10.646 --> 00:46:12.356
And I'll come back for you.

571
00:46:16.026 --> 00:46:17.027
Agreed?

572
00:46:28.205 --> 00:46:29.957
"Cell 3"

573
00:46:35.796 --> 00:46:37.256
"(Allison Becker).

574
00:46:38.799 --> 00:46:42.636
You are accused and
convicted of breaking

575
00:46:42.719 --> 00:46:45.305
our community's fundamental law.

576
00:46:46.181 --> 00:46:48.892
Any verbal request to
leave the silo is approved.

577
00:46:50.727 --> 00:46:52.563
but it cannot be retracted.

578
00:46:54.815 --> 00:46:58.402
Once spoken. it becomes
a final decision.

579
00:47:01.446 --> 00:47:03.115
You were asked to
go out to clean

580
00:47:03.615 --> 00:47:06.410
and we gave you the
necessary tools to do so.

581
00:47:07.244 --> 00:47:09.746
But we cannot
force you to clean.

582
00:47:09.830 --> 00:47:14.209
Once you leave the airlock. you
are outside the silo's authority."

583
00:47:27.472 --> 00:47:29.391
"We don't know why we are here.

584
00:47:32.269 --> 00:47:34.479
We don't know who
built the silo.

585
00:47:36.440 --> 00:47:40.360
We don't know why the situation
outside the silo is as it is.

586
00:47:44.656 --> 00:47:46.158
We don't know...

587
00:47:49.286 --> 00:47:51.538
when it will be safe to go out.

588
00:47:53.665 --> 00:47:55.918
All we know is that that
day has not come yet.

589
00:47:57.211 --> 00:47:59.379
(Allison Becker).

590
00:48:02.508 --> 00:48:06.637
On behalf of the people of
the silo. I hope you clean

591
00:48:07.429 --> 00:48:12.893
so we can see better the world
outside our safe haven as it is

592
00:48:12.976 --> 00:48:15.062
and to remember

593
00:48:16.063 --> 00:48:20.567
that here is safety
and outside is danger."

594
00:48:24.905 --> 00:48:26.365
Do you have any final words?

595
00:48:29.993 --> 00:48:30.994
I love you.

596
00:48:34.289 --> 00:48:35.499
I love you.

597
00:53:00.347 --> 00:53:01.348
Yeah!

598
00:54:01.867 --> 00:54:05.537
"Two years later"

599
00:54:36.652 --> 00:54:38.237
There is something
you should see.

600
00:54:38.737 --> 00:54:42.241
George Wilkins. who Allison
went to help at the market.

601
00:54:42.324 --> 00:54:44.368
- We brought him in and...
- Yeah. I know who he is.

602
00:54:44.451 --> 00:54:47.204
He got a transfer to the
mechanical department last year.

603
00:54:48.372 --> 00:54:49.456
Okay.

604
00:54:49.540 --> 00:54:50.707
"Citizen (George Wilkins)"

605
00:54:50.791 --> 00:54:56.588
He is dead. He fell off
the railing near level 120.

606
00:54:56.672 --> 00:54:59.091
Accident? Suicide?

607
00:54:59.842 --> 00:55:00.968
I don't know.

608
00:55:02.594 --> 00:55:05.097
- What does Hank say?
- He didn't say much.

609
00:55:05.180 --> 00:55:06.723
No one saw him fall.

610
00:55:08.225 --> 00:55:10.394
Tell me the part you're hiding.

611
00:55:13.981 --> 00:55:16.692
There is an engineer
who says it's murder.

612
00:55:37.212 --> 00:55:38.755
Where is the engineer?

613
00:55:40.048 --> 00:55:40.924
She couldn't come.

614
00:55:41.425 --> 00:55:45.053
It took us a day to walk here. She
could have cleared her schedule.

615
00:55:45.554 --> 00:55:46.722
Something came up.

616
00:55:52.686 --> 00:55:53.687
Okay.

617
00:56:00.986 --> 00:56:03.363
Meeting us isn't optional. Hank.

618
00:56:03.447 --> 00:56:06.450
She says this man was murdered.
We have to talk to her.

619
00:56:06.533 --> 00:56:07.534
What came up?

620
00:56:08.952 --> 00:56:11.246
The engine. It's
causing her problems.

621
00:56:13.165 --> 00:56:14.249
What is her job?

622
00:56:14.333 --> 00:56:16.752
Well. she ensures that everyone
in the silo stays alive.

623
00:56:41.026 --> 00:56:42.027
That's it.

624
00:56:43.445 --> 00:56:44.821
- What's her name?
- What?

625
00:56:45.614 --> 00:56:47.157
What's her name?

626
00:56:47.241 --> 00:56:49.952
Juliette. Juliette Nichols.

627
00:57:13.725 --> 00:57:15.602
What happened between you two?

628
00:57:18.480 --> 00:57:20.858
For two years. all
your feelings died.

629
00:57:23.777 --> 00:57:25.529
Then you met Juliette Nichols.

630
00:57:27.030 --> 00:57:30.909
- I only just started listening.
- To what?

631
00:57:31.660 --> 00:57:36.123
To Allison and what
she tried to tell me.

632
00:57:37.416 --> 00:57:39.334
I won't tell you
what she said to me.

633
00:57:39.418 --> 00:57:43.630
All you need to know is
that I will find her.

634
00:57:45.090 --> 00:57:46.341
Do you want to find her?

635
00:57:47.259 --> 00:57:49.178
There she is.

636
00:57:51.972 --> 00:57:53.182
I'm sorry.

637
00:57:55.767 --> 00:57:58.228
As much as I love
you. you bastard.

638
00:57:59.980 --> 00:58:01.481
I love Allison more.

639
00:58:05.777 --> 00:58:10.616
Whether that's really
her outside or not.

640
00:58:11.783 --> 00:58:13.577
I'm finished either way.

641
00:58:14.703 --> 00:58:16.622
I must know the truth.

642
00:58:17.305 --> 00:59:17.754
